# Volunteer Security Projects Repository

## Overview
This repository documents volunteer cybersecurity and technical support activities performed for friends, family members, and community organizations. The goal of these projects is to assist individuals in recovering from common security issues, improving system security, and promoting basic cybersecurity awareness.

These scenarios are anonymized and presented for educational purposes to demonstrate practical security troubleshooting, incident response thinking, and community-based technical support.

---

## Community Partnership: Local Library Support

As part of my volunteer cybersecurity activities, I partner with my local public library to assist community members experiencing computer-related security issues.

On weekends—especially Saturdays—community members frequently visit the library seeking help with suspicious pop-ups, slow computers, browser issues, and other cybersecurity concerns.

During these sessions, I assist users by:

- Identifying potential security threats
- Investigating suspicious browser activity or system behavior
- Guiding users through safe browsing practices
- Checking system security settings
- Assisting with malware cleanup and browser security improvements

These volunteer interactions provide an opportunity to educate community members on digital safety while applying real-world cybersecurity troubleshooting and incident response techniques.

